cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SOC, cs.DB, cs.CR 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with evaluating user reputation in online social lives. It may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves ranking and evaluating user ratings. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) as it deals with social behavior in online rating systems. It may also be relevant to cs.DB (Databases) as it involves grouping and analyzing large amounts of data. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it addresses spamming attacks in online rating systems.
